article.description:
Takia Starks scored 22 points to help No.
22 Texas A&M beat Nebraska 73-64 Wednesday night in the
quarterfinals of the women's Big 12 tournament.
article.headline: Aggies stop Huskers, advance to Big 12 semis
article.linkText: Aggies stop Huskers, advance to Big 12 semis
article.story:
DALLAS (AP) -- Freshman Takia Starks scored 22 points to help No.
22 Texas A&M beat Nebraska 73-64 Wednesday night in the
quarterfinals of the women's Big 12 tournament.

Morenike Atunrase added 21 points and Danielle Gant had 16
rebounds for the Aggies (23-7), who will face No. 10 Baylor in
Thursday's semifinals.

Kiera Hardy had 28 points to lead Nebraska (17-12). Kelsey
Griffin scored 15 and TK LaFleur added 10.

The Cornhuskers pulled to 43-41 before the Aggies put together a
19-8 run midway through the second half for a 62-49 lead. Starks
scored seven points during the spurt.

Texas A&M maintained at least a seven-point lead the rest of the
way, converting 10 of its last 11 free throws.

The Aggies went 17-for-30 from the field in the second half and
finished with a 47-30 rebounding edge.

Nebraska took a 29-27 lead on Hardy's basket with 8 seconds left
in the first half, giving her 16 at the break.
